'''''True Tori''''' is an American  [[Reality television#Documentary-style|docu-series]] starring [[Tori Spelling]] and [[Dean McDermott]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2014/03/31/true-tori-lifetime-docu-series/|title='True Tori': Tori Spelling's new 'real-time' Lifetime docu-series to show life amid scandal|last=Perlman|first=Jake|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=March 31, 2014|accessdate=April 23, 2014}}</ref> It premiered on April 22, 2014, on [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]].<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/03/31/reality-series-true-tori-starring-tori-spelling-to-premiere-april-22-on-lifetime/249398/|title=Reality Series 'True Tori' Starring Tori Spelling to Premiere April 22 on Lifetime|last=Bibel|first=Sara|work=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=March 31, 2014|accessdate=April 23, 2014}}</ref> The series ostensibly chronicles the couple's life from three weeks after McDermott left for rehab and highlights the apparent uncertainty of their marriage due to an alleged affair.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/534056/tori-spelling-i-don-t-know-if-my-marriage-will-have-a-happy-ending|title=Tori Spelling: I Don't Know If My Marriage Will Have a Happy Ending|last=Toomey|first=Alyssa|work=[[E! News]]|date=April 21, 2014|accessdate=April 23, 2014}}</ref> The first season consists of 8 episodes.<ref>{{cite web|title=''True Tori'' Season 1 episodes|url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/true-tori/episodes-season-1/651329|website=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=June 4, 2014}}</ref>

The series has been renewed for a second 8-episode season, which premiered on October 21, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.eonline.com/news/578276/true-tori-returning-for-a-second-season-as-tori-spelling-and-dean-mcdermott-search-for-honesty|title=''True Tori'' Returning for a Second Season as Tori Spelling and Dean McDermott Search for "Honesty"|last=Bricker |first=Tierney|work=E! News|date=September 11, 2014|accessdate=November 5, 2014}}</ref> The second season continued to focus on Tori and Dean's failing marriage as they try to rebuild their relationship and make decisions that would be the best for them and their four children. Tori tries to find her "true self" and ways how to juggle between her family relationships and business ventures.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/09/11/true-tori-returns-for-a-raw-and-revealing-season-two-on-october-21/301956/|title='True Tori' Returns for a Raw and Revealing Season Two on October 21|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|work=TV by the Numbers|date=September 11, 2014|accessdate=November 5, 2014}}</ref>

